 has acquired ukbased ctc aviation group in a deal worth  million £ million in cash the acquisition aims at enhancing its commercial aviation training operations and strengthening its international presencectc aviation has been renamed l ctc ltd and integrated into the company’s electronic systems segmentl ctc aviation has a worldwide reputation in providing specialized and innovative solutions related to pilot training and crew resourcing services to major airlines and retail customers its integration into l’s commercial aviation training business which already includes l link uk ­ a worldclass provider of flighttraining simulation devices will strengthen l communications’ foothold as a leading provider of flight training and simulation servicesl ctc expects sales of  million in  and  million in  being a highmargin business it has the potential to generate operating margins more than that of the entire electronic systems segment hence the acquisition is a strategic fit for the company as it strengthens its training solutions across a wide range of military and commercial platforms the company expects l ctc to add approximately  million to its total sales this yeargiven that l communications’ business is primarily driven by contracts from the us government a tepid defense budget scenario has compelled it to expand and consolidate its international presence a steady flow of foreign contracts will thus help to counter the sequestration impact at homerecently the company posted weak firstquarter results with earnings falling  year over year hurt by a sales decline in each of its four segments the company also lowered its revenue and earnings guidance for  although growth slowed down in the first quarter its strategy of gradually expanding its commercial and international operations has partially offset some of the domestic declinethe company’s international and commercial sales represented about  of its consolidated net sales in the firstquarter  up from  in firstquart